            array('id' => '1','category_id' => '23','title' => 'Poultry','slug' => 'poultry','preview' => '/uploads/24/03/dmPXpOkEuz0uhVb0oQH7.jpg','cover_image' => '/uploads/24/03/KdMTTANf6MjAq95umCk5.jpg','address' => '132, Kingston, New York.','total_units' => '100','invest_amount' => '100','expire_date' => '2024-12-31 00:00:00','status' => '1','accept_new_investor' => '1','meta' => NULL,'faqs' => '[{"qns":"What are the primary types of chicken raised in poultry farming?","ans":"The two primary types of chickens raised in poultry farming are broilers, which are raised for meat production, and layers, which are raised for egg production."},{"qns":"How long does it take to raise chickens for meat production (broilers)?","ans":"Broilers are typically ready for market between 6 to 8 weeks of age, depending on factors such as breed, nutrition, and management practices."},{"qns":"How many eggs can a laying hen produce in a year?","ans":"The egg production of laying hens varies depending on factors such as breed, age, and environmental conditions. On average, a laying hen can produce anywhere from 250 to 300 eggs per year."},{"qns":"What are some common diseases that affect chickens, and how are they managed?","ans":"Common diseases in chickens include Newcastle disease, infectious bronchitis, coccidiosis, and avian influenza. Management strategies include vaccination, biosecurity measures, and prompt diagnosis and treatment by a veterinarian."}]','created_at' => '2024-03-25 10:09:54','updated_at' => '2024-03-25 10:11:59'),
            array('id' => '2','category_id' => '24','title' => 'Dairy farm','slug' => 'dairy-farm','preview' => '/uploads/24/03/JSm86hsI9L8ZjEYCHeTx.jpg','cover_image' => '/uploads/24/03/KgzivT2oQNiGn82DJCNw.jpg','address' => '132, Kingston, New York.','total_units' => '50','invest_amount' => '500','expire_date' => '2024-12-31 00:00:00','status' => '1','accept_new_investor' => '1','meta' => NULL,'faqs' => '[{"qns":"What are the factors influencing the profitability of investing in a dairy farm agro?","ans":"Several factors can impact the profitability of investing in a dairy firm agro. These include milk prices, which are influenced by supply and demand dynamics, feed costs, labor expenses, and overhead costs associated with maintaining the herd and infrastructure. Additionally, efficiency improvements through technology adoption, scale of operations, and effective risk management strategies play crucial roles in enhancing profitability."},{"qns":"How can I assess the sustainability practices of a dairy firm before investing?","ans":"Evaluating the sustainability practices of a dairy firm involves examining various aspects, such as animal welfare standards, environmental stewardship, and social responsibility initiatives. Investors can look for certifications like organic or Fair Trade, assess the farm\'s waste management practices, energy efficiency measures, and water conservation efforts. Transparency in reporting and adherence to industry standards for sustainability can also indicate a firm\'s commitment to responsible practices."},{"qns":"What are the potential regulatory considerations when investing in a dairy firm agro?","ans":"Regulatory considerations for investing in a dairy firm agro vary by jurisdiction and can encompass a range of issues such as food safety regulations, environmental regulations, animal welfare standards, and labor laws. Investors should be aware of compliance requirements related to milk processing and distribution, zoning regulations for farm operations, permits for waste management, and adherence to labor standards. Engaging legal and regulatory experts familiar with the dairy industry can help navigate these complexities."}]','created_at' => '2024-03-25 10:28:47','updated_at' => '2024-03-25 10:28:47'),
