            array('id' => '1','project_id' => '1','key' => 'short_description','value' => 'Poultry farming is the form of animal husbandry which raises domesticated birds such as chickens, ducks, turkeys and geese to produce meat or eggs for food.','created_at' => NULL,'updated_at' => NULL),
            array('id' => '2','project_id' => '1','key' => 'main_description','value' => '<p>Poultry farming, specifically focusing on chicken rearing, is a dynamic and vital component of the agricultural industry worldwide. From small-scale backyard operations to large-scale commercial ventures, chicken poultry farming encompasses a diverse array of practices tailored to meet the demands of varying markets and consumers.</p><p>At its core, chicken poultry farming involves the systematic raising of domesticated chickens for their meat, eggs, or both. The process typically begins with the acquisition of day-old chicks, which are then carefully nurtured and managed throughout their lifecycle.</p>','created_at' => NULL,'updated_at' => NULL),
