            array('id' => '25','project_id' => '4','key' => 'short_description','value' => 'Paddy harvest refers to the process of gathering mature rice plants, known as paddy, from fields after they have reached full maturity and drying them for further processing. This process typically involves cutting the rice plants, also known as rice straw, with specialized machinery such as combine harvesters or manually using sickles or other cutting tools. After harvesting, the paddy undergoes drying to reduce its moisture content, which is crucial for preventing spoilage and ensuring.','created_at' => NULL,'updated_at' => NULL),
            array('id' => '26','project_id' => '4','key' => 'main_description','value' => '<p>"Paddy harvest" refers to the process of gathering mature rice plants, known as paddy, from fields after they have reached full maturity and drying them for further processing. This process typically involves cutting the rice plants, also known as rice straw, with specialized machinery such as combine harvesters or manually using sickles or other cutting tools. After harvesting, the paddy undergoes drying to reduce its moisture content, which is crucial for preventing spoilage and ensuring optimal storage conditions. Once dried, the rice kernels are separated from the husks through milling, resulting in the production of brown rice, which can be further processed into white rice or other rice products for consumption. Paddy harvest is a critical step in rice production, marking the culmination of months of cultivation and the beginning of the post-harvest processing phase.</p>','created_at' => NULL,'updated_at' => NULL),
